| ... | ... | ... | ... |

*Generated: YYYY-MM-DD | Tiers: N T1, N T2, N T3, N T4 | Elements: N/N | Source: {writer.kind}*
```

## B. Quality Assertions — Machine-Checkable

After writing, verify EVERY assertion before saving:

| # | Assertion | How to Check | Hard/Soft |
|---|-----------|-------------|-----------|
| 1 | All 6 `## N.` sections present (1 through 6) | Count `## 1.` through `## 6.` headers | HARD |
| 2 | Every Element description ends with `(Tier N — source)` | Grep for `\(Tier [1-5] —` in Section 3 | HARD |
| 3 | Element table has 5 columns: `# \| Element \| Type \| Nullable \| Description` | Check header row | HARD |
| 4 | Element count matches `column_count` in frontmatter | Compare table-row count vs frontmatter | HARD |
| 5 | Section 4.2 has pipeline ASCII diagram | Check for code block with `→` or `▼` | HARD |
| 6 | Section 4.3 cross-check summary line present | Grep for `parsed=` `runtime=` `mismatches=` | HARD |
| 7 | Footer has tier breakdown counts matching frontmatter | Compare `*Tiers:` line vs frontmatter | HARD |
| 8 | Property table has at least UC Object, Type, Writer, Primary upstream | Check for these rows | HARD |
| 9 | `.review-needed.md` does NOT contain `## 3. Elements` | If it does, content is in the WRONG file | HARD |
| 10 | `.lineage.md` exists and was written BEFORE `.md` | Check file existence + mtime | HARD |
| 11 | For passthrough columns, the description text MATCHES the upstream wiki's Element description byte-for-byte | Grep upstream wiki for the same column and diff | HARD (assertion 11 enforces tier transitivity) |
| 12 | Section 2 collapsed to "Pure passthrough" for views where every column is passthrough/rename | Check transform classifications in `.lineage.md` | SOFT |
| 13 | Every column description falls into exactly ONE of three buckets: (a) byte-equal to upstream wiki for the same column (passthrough/rename/cast); (b) cites a source-code line range OR a SQL operator OR a quoted SQL fragment from the cached Phase-2 snapshot (CASE/arithmetic/aggregate/window/coalesce/udf); (c) exact-matches the null-with-provenance template `Source: {upstream_fqn}.{col}. No upstream wiki cached as of {YYYY-MM-DD}.` (terminal-no-wiki upstream). Anything else is AI-inferred and forbidden by §6 No-Inference Contract in `05-generate-doc.mdc`. | Run `python tools/uc_pipelines/validate_pipeline_wiki.py --assert-no-inference --wiki <path>` — exits non-zero on any unclassifiable column | HARD |

**If ANY HARD assertion fails: delete the file and regenerate. Do not patch.**

**Assertion 13 hard contract**: There is no fourth bucket. A description that "looks plausible" but does NOT match (a), (b), or (c) is a Principle XI violation per the constitution and a hard validator failure. This applies to the 3-object pilot regression as much as to any new object — backward compatibility is enforced.

## C. Dictionary Inline Values Rule

Same as `dwh-semantic-doc/GOLDEN-REFERENCE.mdc` §C:

| Dictionary Size | Rule | Example |
|----------------|------|---------|
| **<=15 distinct values** | Inline key=value pairs in the description | `1=Regular, 2=CopyMe, 3=Social Index, 4=Fund (Dictionary.MirrorType)` |
| **>15 distinct values** | Name the join target only, describe what it represents | `FK to dim_country. Resolves to country name.` |

## D. Tier Suffix Convention — UC Pipeline Specifics

The tier suffix `(Tier N — origin)` lives at the END of every Element description. Use these origin patterns:

| Column situation | RIGHT | WRONG |
|---|---|---|
| Passthrough of a DWH gold-mirror column whose origin is `Trade.PositionTbl` | `(Tier 1 — Trade.PositionTbl)` | `(Tier 1 — main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction)` |
| Passthrough of a column with no upstream wiki (genuinely new column added in this UC object) | `(Tier 2 — main.{schema}.{this_object})` | `(Tier 2 — view DDL)` |
| CASE/CAST/arithmetic over an upstream column | `(Tier 2 — main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction)` | `(Tier 2 — view DDL)` |
| Multi-source UNION ALL | `(Tier 2 — main.dwh...fact_customeraction / main.etoro_kpi_prep.passive_actions_enriched)` | `(Tier 2 — view DDL)` |
| Pure literal (`current_date`, `1`, `'PROD'`) | `(Tier 2 — main.{schema}.{this_object})` | `(Tier 2 — view DDL)` |
| join_enriched column from a join source with a wiki | inherit join source's origin tier tag | `(Tier 1 — JOIN)` |

The origin **always** names a data-producing entity (a table or, in the literal/synthesized case, this object itself). It never names "view DDL" or "notebook" as such — those are evidence types cited inside the description; the tier suffix names the data origin.

## E. Anti-Patterns — What Drift Looks Like

### E1. Missing Tier Suffix

```
WRONG: | 3 | enrichment_flag | STRING | YES | Flag for copy vs manual actions |
RIGHT: | 3 | enrichment_flag | STRING | YES | Flag derived from ActionTypeID — 'copy' for {2,5}, 'manual' otherwise (CASE in view DDL L42). (Tier 2 — main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction) |
```

### E2. Synapse-mirror as origin

```
WRONG: | 1 | HistoryID | BIGINT | NO | Source-system history id. (Tier 1 — main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction) |
RIGHT: | 1 | HistoryID | BIGINT | NO | Source-system history id from `History.Credit` (non-unique — never use as PK). (Tier 1 — History.Credit) |
```

Tier transitivity: the Synapse mirror is a RELAY, not the origin. Always inherit through.

### E3. Wiki content in sidecar

```
WRONG: Writing the Elements table into {Object}.review-needed.md
RIGHT: The .md file gets the full 6-section wiki. The .review-needed.md gets ONLY
       UNVERIFIED items, Tier 4 candidates needing review, parser warnings, and
       reviewer correction notes. It is a lightweight checklist, NOT a duplicate wiki.
```

### E4. Bloated Section 2 for passthrough views

```
WRONG: Filling Section 2 with subsections that just re-describe the upstream's logic.
RIGHT: For pure-passthrough VIEWs: "Pure passthrough of `main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction` — no transformation logic. See upstream wiki for source-system rules: knowledge/synapse/Wiki/DWH_dbo/Tables/Fact_CustomerAction.md." Section 2 = 1 sentence.
```

The point of this pack is to NOT duplicate upstream content. Inherit, link, and only add value where this object actually adds value.

### E5. Missing pipeline diagram

```
WRONG: ## 4. Lineage
       Sourced from upstream UC objects.

RIGHT: ## 4. Lineage
       ### 4.2 Pipeline ASCII Diagram
       ```
       Production: etoro.History.Credit / etoro.Trade.OpenPositionEndOfDay / …
              ↓ Generic Pipeline (Bronze)
       Synapse: DWH_dbo.Fact_CustomerAction  ── documented at knowledge/synapse/Wiki/DWH_dbo/Tables/Fact_CustomerAction.md
              ↓ Generic Pipeline (Gold export → Delta)
       main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction
              ↓ view_definition (this object)
       main.etoro_kpi_prep.v_fact_customeraction_enriched  ←── this object
              ↓ JOIN dim_position, UNION passive_actions_enriched
       main.etoro_kpi_prep.v_fact_customeraction_w_metrics  (downstream)
       ```
```

Concrete chain with object names, not vague prose.
